  TITLE     A mutation in the viral sensor 2'-5'-oligoadenylate synthetase 2
            causes failure of lactation
  JOURNAL   PLoS Genet 13 (11), e1007072 (2017)
   PUBMED   29117179
  REMARK    GeneRIF: A non-synonymous mutation in Oas2 (I405N) in the viral
            sensor Oas2 was found and the mutation caused post-partum failure
            of lactation in healthy mice with otherwise normally developed
            mammary glands, characterized by greatly reduced milk protein
            synthesis coupled with epithelial cell death, inhibition of
            proliferation and a robust interferon response. The mutation
            activates the OAS2 pathway.
            Publication Status: Online-Only
